The selection drifts through drone, minimalism, ambient, electroacoustic, folk, and sacred music, featuring many friends and collaborators whose work continues to shape and inspire them. The first half features Kali’s selections, with Drew taking over in the second.

nts1.d: Marking the release of Night School’s new compilation “All The Young Droids: Junkshop Synth Pop 1978-1985” with an hour of sounds featured – uncovering the underbelly of the epoch-defining sound of synthesizer pop in the early 1980s, with DIY efforts, obscure chart flops, punk experiments and more, selected by ex-Felt, Lush, and The Jesus And Mary Chain guitarist Phil King.

nts1.n: CHANNELING W/ IVAN SMAGGHE & NATHAN GREGORY WILKINS (R)
nts1.d: Old friends and hapless mavericks Ivan Smagghe and Nathan Gregory Wilkins present a fortnightly window into their ramshackle musical world. A show with absolutely no rules (as they'd only break them). We love the unmixable, old & new. We are oddballs and we love you.

Two hours of uncanny pop and eerie synth minimalism from Sheffield pioneers The Human League. 
Formed in Sheffield in 1977, The Human League started as an experimental, post-industrial synth trio. After key members left in 1980, Philip Oakey rebuilt the band with two teenage vocalists, shifting towards the more charismatic (and commercially viable) new wave sound that thrust them into the mainstream. Their 1981 album Dare and the hit “Don’t You Want Me” went on to define early ’80s electronic pop. 
Selected and mixed by Aki Yamouridis.

nts2.n: EVERYDAY A FEELING W/ SPELLS FOR NATURE
nts2.d: everyday a feeling is an hour of meditative & spacious sounds for quiet nights at home.

If I can pause long enough to light an incense, I know I'm going to be okay. It’s the only 5-second ritual I have that immediately grounds me. The smoke always clears something up. These songs embody that feeling. I play them on loop when I need comfort. They always clear something up. Always.

The sounds of peace are the quiet sounds of domesticity - objects moving in space, half-utterances, fragments of melody. Brief glimpses of beauty. A few throughlines: 00s glitch and folktronica, spoken word, field recordings.
Fragments of serenity to gently soothe the chaos.
back home from the party thinking "man I love this place"

Ciao sono santapazienza, una ricercatrice accanita di musica di ogni genere ma non comune. Attualmente vivo a Torino e ho 25 anni.
Ho preparato questo set prima di andare a dormire, per fare bei sogni.

Hi everyone, I think it’s very hard not to get distracted with everything demanding our attention. Now more than ever, we’ve got to take back our time and attention to focus on what’s important. I’ve started collecting songs that bring me peace in troubled times. May it help you too <3

This set is inspired by 90s liquid jungle. I find this music one very effective way to calm my mind in times where war, warcrimes, cruelty, injustice and fear are on display. 
I hope this mix has the same effect for the listeners. even though it may seem hard, and in this injustice, for some it is impossible because they struggle to survive, I still think its important to remember that we are capable of making and enjoying beautiful and meaningful art. and that it can make us come together.

subtle.d: Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
Hailing from Belfast but making moves in Nottingham, Nikki O is a DJ and radio presenter whose sets blend 4/4 rhythms, breakbeats, and the bassier side of techno.
